8 dead in northwest China road accident | Shanghai Daily
Follow us @  | Shanghai Call Center: 962288 |  Mobile Version  |  THU, APR 18, 2013
URUMQI, Sept. 21 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed in a road accident on Sunday in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, local authorities said.
The tragedy happened at around 4:30 p.m. Sunday when a truck slammed head-on into a minibus at an intersection in Toksun County, Turpan Prefecture, according to the Xinjiang police.
Eight people in the minibus died at the scene. An investigation into the accident is under way.

